  "description": "Bird was about 10' off the ground, foraging in the newly leafed out branches, moving along branch looking for bugs, moving quickly around in a contained area about 5' in diameter the whole time. No calling, focused on eating. It was a YEWA within 2' of it and a YRWA about 10' away but they didn't seem to mind each other. There was also a porcupine in the tree about 10' from where it was feeding. Light wind. Clearly a female warber by body shape and pale coloring. ID'd when I got home and could look closely at the pictures and my book.",
